ooks like existing tests don’t use Project, which I need to keep in mind. I should probably avoid having tests that directly reflect that. Maybe I won’t need the `@TempDir` import after all. I’ll write a file to ensure Java 21 compatibility while double-checking that the source might still work. Since the existing tests use text blocks and readAllBytes, that seems fine. I also want to assert that the external resolver can indeed parse the XML catalog correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing AntClassLoader issues**\\n\\nI see there might be a potential issue with the AntClassLoader created in the getCatalogResolver method that needs to be cleaned up. It appears to create a loader that isn't cleaned up after use, but this isn't a concern for tests. That's good to know! I'll need to edit the build.gradle file and also write a test to ensure everything is functioning correctly. Let’s get on it!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fvQxNwN9piOp2XW5CRUaCjtf|fc_0de4b39fe136b6300169fb94289d6c819ebd78c613db16d840", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "    testImplementation \"ant:ant:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n", "newText": "    testImplementation \"ant:ant:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'xml-resolver:xml-resolver:1.2'\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1608, "output": 928, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46568, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778095129134, "responseId": "resp_0de4b39fe136b6300169fb941a8b88819eacd3da9b1a3bab77"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fvQxNwN9piOp2XW5CRUaCjtf|fc_0de4b39fe136b6300169fb94289d6c819ebd78c613db16d840", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type"