[thinking] I'm considering what happens if a parent class loader isn’t set. The class is in the native image classpath, so it should ideally be found by the application class loader. But if there’s no parent set for AntClassLoader, that complicates things. I wonder how often this occurs and what the implications would be. It's a bit tricky to navigate, so I’ll have to keep an eye out for this situation.
